{"surah":{"number":60,"name":"الممتحنة","englishName":"Al-Mumtahanah","englishTranslation":"She that is to be examined","ayahCount":13},"sources":["Quran.com API v4 (word-by-word Uthmani + English glosses + word audio)","AlQuran.cloud / Tanzil quran-uthmani (independent text verification)","AlQuran.cloud / Saheeh International (flowing English translation)","Quranic Arabic Corpus morphology (word roots)"],"generatedAt":"2026-07-03T04:01:22.624Z","ayahs":[{"number":1,"translation":"O you who have believed, do not take My enemies and your enemies as allies, extending to them affection while they have disbelieved in what came to you of the truth, having driven out the Prophet and yourselves [only] because you believe in Allah, your Lord. If you have come out for jihad in My cause and seeking means to My approval, [take them not as friends]. You confide to them affection, but I am most knowing of what you have concealed and what you have declared. And whoever does it among you has certainly strayed from the soundness of the way.","words":[{"position":1,"arabic":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا","english":"O you","translit":"yāayyuhā","root":"أيي"},{"position":2,"arabic":"ٱلَّذِينَ","english":"who","translit":"alladhīna","root":""},{"position":3,"arabic":"ءَامَنُوا۟","english":"believe","translit":"āmanū","root":"أمن"},{"position":4,"arabic":"لَا","english":"(Do) not","translit":"lā","root":""},{"position":5,"arabic":"تَتَّخِذُوا۟","english":"take","translit":"tattakhidhū","root":"أخذ"},{"position":6,"arabic":"عَدُوِّى","english":"My enemies","translit":"ʿaduwwī","root":"عدو"},{"position":7,"arabic":"وَعَدُوَّكُمْ","english":"and your enemies","translit":"waʿaduwwakum","root":"عدو"},{"position":8,"arabic":"أَوْلِيَآءَ","english":"(as) allies","translit":"awliyāa","root":"ولي"},{"position":9,"arabic":"تُلْقُونَ","english":"offering","translit":"tul'qūna","root":"لقي"},{"position":10,"arabic":"إِلَيْهِم","english":"them","translit":"ilayhim","root":""},{"position":11,"arabic":"بِٱلْمَوَدَّ